    • Constructor Detail

      • Contract

        public Contract​(java.lang.String name,
                java.lang.String binary,
                boolean isOnlyRuntime,
                java.lang.String address)
         throws NotSolidityContractException
        Creates a contract with the given inputs. The bytecode is divided between metadata, constructor, runtime and remaining data. Then the cfg is built.
        Parameters:
        name - contract name
        binary - hexadecimal string with the bytecode
        isOnlyRuntime - if it is only runtime code or creation code
        address - address of the contract if it's deployed in the blockchain
        Throws:
        NotSolidityContractException - If the bytecode has not been generated by solc
